The paper discusses secret sharing, which is a cryptographic discipline related to information theory (cs.IT) and computer security (cs.CR). It also mentions systems of variables, which could be related to data structures (cs.DS). The paper proposes an extension to the partial information lattice, which is a framework for information decomposition, and this could be relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
